[3] Bird - Michigan
Date: Tue 11 May 2004
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <arodriguezm@SaludFMV.org>
Source: WZZM News online, Tue 11 May 2004 [edited]
<http://www.wzzm13.com/news/news_article.aspx?storyid=26776>


Michigan: West Vile virus-positive crow found in Saginaw county
-----------------------------------------------
State officials say West Nile virus has made its 1st appearance of the year
in Michigan. Health authorities detected the virus in a dead crow found in
the town of Tittabawassee Township, Saginaw County, last week [early May
2004]. The head of mosquito control in Saginaw County says that it's
unclear whether the discovery is an indicator for a bad season in 2004 for
the potentially fatal virus. Michigan had only 19 reported human cases of
West Nile virus infection in 2003, including 2 deaths. In 2002, the state
had 644 reported cases of the virus and at least 51 deaths.

